            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once your potatoes are almost cooked, heat another pan with a matching lid with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into a bowl, and once the pan is hot, add the<strong> eggs</strong> in one go</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking, then remove from the heat and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
